Is this a reasonable understanding of EIP-3540's Container Specification section (in something resembling EBNF)?

```ebnf
container = magic, version, section_headers, section_headers_terminator, body;

section_headers = section_header, { section_header };
section_header = section_kind, section_size | section_size_list;
section_size = non_zero_byte;
section_size_list = section_size_list_count, section_size, { section_size };
section_size_list_count = byte, byte;
section_size = byte, byte;

section_headers_terminator = "\0";

body = section, { section };
section = { byte };

magic = "\xEF\x00";
version = non_zero_byte;

non_zero_short = (* TODO *);
non_zero_byte = "\x01" | "\x02" (* ... *) | "\xFF";
byte = "\x00" | non_zero_byte;
```
